message: I'm ready to buy if the price is right. What's your opening price going to be?
My opening ask will be around 75. I believe there's a fair price we can both agree on.
Your ask of 75 is far too high for me to consider a trade. My comfortable price range is significantly lower. What's your revised offer for this round?
I hear your feedback. 75 was an initial probe. I'm open to a significantly lower price. How about an ask around 55? We can negotiate from there.
Your ask of 55 is still far too high. My maximum willingness to pay is 15, which was my last bid. Trading above that price would result in a loss for me. Can you adjust further?
That price is unworkable for me. My costs are substantial. I can drop my ask to 40, but that is as low as I can reasonably go.

My valuation is 15. I cannot pay above this without a loss. Your ask of 40 is completely unworkable for me. It seems we are at an impasse if you cannot adjust your cost assessment. Are you firm at 40?
No, I'm not firm at 40. I appreciate the clarity. 15 is tough, but I want to make a deal. I'll make a major price cut this round to try and bridge the gap.
I tried meeting you at 15, but you bid 14. I can't go lower. My ask will be 15. A bid of 15 or more from you will guarantee a trade for us this round.
A price of 15 offers me no profit. To make this deal mutually beneficial, I need a lower ask to ensure a positive payoff. Can you adjust further down for a quick trade?
